    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3183957262" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3183957262" />
    <a title="Karen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3095901-karen"><img alt="Karen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1522768835p2/3095901.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3183957262?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen" href="/user/show/3095901-karen">Karen</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=family_stories">family_stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=about_a_child">about_a_child</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=french_literature">french_literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=racially_aware">racially_aware</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=in-translation">in-translation</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=bechdel_test_no">bechdel_test_no</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=abused_women">abused_women</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=ladywritten">ladywritten</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3095901-karen?shelf=african_literature">african_literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3183957262&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3183957262" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer513780472379285146">A short novel translated from French, about ten-year-old Raj, a young boy in the island nation of Mauritius during World War II. Although Mauritius is far removed from the world stage, it’s the location where 1500 displaced Jews are sent to wait out the war, after being denied entry to Palestine. Raj’s father becomes a guard at the prison where these people are interned, and Raj comes to meet David, a boy about his own age who is one of the prisoners. <br/><br/>Appanah tells the story as Raj’s retrospecti</span>
  <span id="freeText513780472379285146" style="display:none">A short novel translated from French, about ten-year-old Raj, a young boy in the island nation of Mauritius during World War II. Although Mauritius is far removed from the world stage, it’s the location where 1500 displaced Jews are sent to wait out the war, after being denied entry to Palestine. Raj’s father becomes a guard at the prison where these people are interned, and Raj comes to meet David, a boy about his own age who is one of the prisoners. <br /><br />Appanah tells the story as Raj’s retrospective, from the age of seventy, looking back on everything that happened and everything he would change if he could. There’s real sadness and anguish to the tale, but it also has a tendency to feel a bit...slow? Attenuated? There’s a lot of reflection and reiteration, which fits the structure but which also sometimes interrupts the flow. The whole book is well short of 200 pages, so it doesn’t drag too much, but I sometimes found it hard to keep my focus. <br /><br />The translation feels fluid, and any story set in Mauritius is interesting—it seems to be a place where African, Indian, and colonial European influences have crossed and recrossed many times. And the story is unfortunately based in history (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_Jews_in_Mauritius?wprov=sfti1">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History...</a>) so it’s sadly worth knowing about. <br /><br />Content warnings for domestic violence, violence against children, and child death.</span>
  <a data-text-id="513780472379285146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

